{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"How do we get people engaged\nin solving global warming?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":5440,"text":"I'd like to start with running\ntwo short experiments with you all."},{"time":10560,"text":"So your task is to notice\nif you feel any difference as I speak."},{"time":15800,"text":"OK?"},{"time":18120,"text":"Here we go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20200,"text":"We are seeing rising\ncarbon dioxide levels,"},{"time":23440,"text":"now about 410 ppms."},{"time":26960,"text":"To avoid the RCP 8.5 scenario,"},{"time":29840,"text":"we need rapid decarbonization."},{"time":33240,"text":"The global carbon budget"},{"time":35320,"text":"for 66 percent likelihood\nto meet the two-degree target"},{"time":38840,"text":"is approximately 800 gigatons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":46200,"text":"OK, now let me try something else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49600,"text":"We are heading for an uninhabitable earth:"},{"time":54520,"text":"monster storms,"},{"time":56640,"text":"killer floods,"},{"time":58400,"text":"devastating wildfires,"},{"time":60720,"text":"crazy heat waves that will cook us\nunder a blazing sun."},{"time":66840,"text":"2017 is already so unexpectedly warm,"},{"time":70520,"text":"it's freaking out climate scientists."},{"time":72840,"text":"We have a three-year window\nto cut emissions, three years."},{"time":76800,"text":"If not, we will soon live\nin a boiling earth, a hellhole."},{"time":84000,"text":"OK. So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86320,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":87840,"text":"Now your task:"},{"time":90600,"text":"How did these ways\nof speaking make you feel?"},{"time":93560,"text":"The first, detached maybe\nor just confused?"},{"time":97680,"text":"What's this guy talking about?"},{"time":100040,"text":"The other, fearful or just numb?"},{"time":104960,"text":"So again, the question I asked:"},{"time":106480,"text":"How do we get people engaged\nin solving global warming?"},{"time":110000,"text":"And why don't these two ways\nof communicating work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114000,"text":"You see, the biggest obstacle\nto dealing with climate disruptions"},{"time":118360,"text":"lies between your ears."},{"time":121360,"text":"Building on a rapidly growing body\nof psychology and social science,"},{"time":125360,"text":"I spent years looking\ninto the five inner defenses"},{"time":129360,"text":"that stop people from engaging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131960,"text":"When people hear news about the climate\ncoming straight at them,"},{"time":135640,"text":"the first defense comes up rapidly:"},{"time":139280,"text":"distance."},{"time":141040,"text":"When we hear about the climate,"},{"time":142600,"text":"we hear about something\nfar away in space --"},{"time":144720,"text":"think Arctic ice, polar bears --"},{"time":147400,"text":"far away in time -- think 2100."},{"time":151320,"text":"It's huge and slow-moving --\nthink gigatons and centuries."},{"time":156480,"text":"So it's not here. It's not now."},{"time":161000,"text":"Since it feels so far away from me,"},{"time":162720,"text":"it seems outside my circle of influence,"},{"time":166520,"text":"so I feel helpless about it."},{"time":168440,"text":"There's nothing I can do."},{"time":171000,"text":"In our everyday lives,"},{"time":172440,"text":"most of us prefer to think\nabout nearer things,"},{"time":175320,"text":"such as our jobs, our kids,"},{"time":177560,"text":"how many likes we get on Facebook."},{"time":180400,"text":"Now, that, that's real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184080,"text":"Next defense is doom."},{"time":188040,"text":"Climate change is usually framed"},{"time":191040,"text":"as a looming disaster,"},{"time":193120,"text":"bringing losses, cost and sacrifice."},{"time":195920,"text":"That makes us fearful."},{"time":198240,"text":"But after the first fear is gone,"},{"time":201720,"text":"my brain soon wants\nto avoid this topic altogether."},{"time":206360,"text":"After 30 years of scary\nclimate change communications,"},{"time":209760,"text":"more than 80 percent of media articles\nstill use disaster framings,"},{"time":214600,"text":"but people habituate to and then --"},{"time":219160,"text":"desensitize"},{"time":220840,"text":"to doom overuse."},{"time":222360,"text":"So many of us are now suffering\na kind of apocalypse fatigue,"},{"time":227080,"text":"getting numb from too much collapse porn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231760,"text":"The third defense is dissonance."},{"time":234800,"text":"Now, if what we know,"},{"time":237720,"text":"that fossil fuel use\ncontributes to global warming,"},{"time":240160,"text":"conflicts with what we do --\ndrive, fly, eat beef --"},{"time":242880,"text":"then so-called\ncognitive dissonance sets in."},{"time":246280,"text":"This is felt as an inner discomfort."},{"time":248200,"text":"We may feel like hypocrites."},{"time":250600,"text":"To get rid of this discomfort,"},{"time":253000,"text":"our brain starts coming up\nwith justifications."},{"time":256160,"text":"So I can say, for instance,"},{"time":258200,"text":"\"My neighbor, he has\na much bigger car than I do.\""},{"time":262480,"text":"Or, \"Changing my diet\ndoesn't amount to anything"},{"time":266320,"text":"if I am the only one to do it.\""},{"time":269720,"text":"Or, I could even want\nto doubt climate science itself."},{"time":273400,"text":"I could say, \"You know,\nclimate is always changing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"So these justifications\nmake us all feel better,"},{"time":281960,"text":"but at the expense"},{"time":284600,"text":"of dismissing what we know."},{"time":286720,"text":"Thus, behavior drives attitudes."},{"time":291920,"text":"My personal cognitive dissonance comes up"},{"time":294680,"text":"when I recognize that I've been\nflying from Oslo to New York"},{"time":298040,"text":"and back to Oslo"},{"time":299320,"text":"in order to speak about the climate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":304000,"text":"For 14 minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":309200,"text":"So that makes me\nwant to move on to denial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311920,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":314200,"text":"So if we keep silent,"},{"time":316000,"text":"ignore or ridicule facts\nabout climate disruptions,"},{"time":320080,"text":"then we might find inner refuge"},{"time":322920,"text":"from fear and guilt."},{"time":325200,"text":"Denial doesn't really come\nfrom lack of intelligence or knowledge."},{"time":328920,"text":"No, denial is a state of mind"},{"time":332240,"text":"in which I may be aware\nof some troubling knowledge,"},{"time":335120,"text":"but I live and act as if I don't know."},{"time":338560,"text":"So you could call it\na kind of double life,"},{"time":341280,"text":"both knowing and not knowing,"},{"time":342800,"text":"and often this is reinforced by others,"},{"time":345160,"text":"my family or community,"},{"time":346600,"text":"agreeing not to raise this tricky topic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351240,"text":"Finally, identity."},{"time":355440,"text":"Alarmed climate activists"},{"time":358680,"text":"demand that government takes action,"},{"time":361000,"text":"either with regulation or carbon taxes."},{"time":363720,"text":"But consider what happens"},{"time":365600,"text":"when people who hold\nconservative values, for instance,"},{"time":369360,"text":"hear from an activist that government\nought to expand even further."},{"time":374760,"text":"Particularly in rich Western democracies,"},{"time":376800,"text":"they are then less likely\nto believe that science."},{"time":381320,"text":"How is that?"},{"time":382680,"text":"Well, if I hold conservative\nvalues, for instance,"},{"time":386120,"text":"I probably prefer big proper cars\nand small government"},{"time":390880,"text":"over tiny, tiny cars and huge government."},{"time":395240,"text":"And if climate science comes and then says"},{"time":398640,"text":"government should expand further,"},{"time":400680,"text":"then I probably\nwill trust that science less."},{"time":406320,"text":"In this way, cultural identity"},{"time":409320,"text":"starts to override the facts."},{"time":411320,"text":"The values eat the facts,"},{"time":413520,"text":"and my identity trumps truth any day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419240,"text":"So, after recognizing\nhow these five D's kill engagement,"},{"time":424280,"text":"how can we move beyond them?"},{"time":427240,"text":"New research shows\nhow we can flip these five defenses"},{"time":430840,"text":"over into key success criteria"},{"time":433000,"text":"for a more brain-friendly\nclimate communication."},{"time":436880,"text":"So this is where it gets really exciting"},{"time":440000,"text":"and where we find the five S's,"},{"time":443040,"text":"the five evidence-based solutions\nfor what does work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448120,"text":"First, we can flip distance to social."},{"time":451960,"text":"We can make climate feel\nnear, personal and urgent"},{"time":455440,"text":"by bringing it home,"},{"time":458520,"text":"and we can do that\nby spreading social norms"},{"time":461640,"text":"that are positive to solutions."},{"time":463800,"text":"If I believe my friends or neighbors,"},{"time":466160,"text":"you guys, will do something,"},{"time":467840,"text":"then I will, too."},{"time":470000,"text":"We can see, for instance,\nthis from rooftop solar panels."},{"time":473360,"text":"They are spreading from neighbor\nto neighbor like a virus."},{"time":476160,"text":"It's contagious."},{"time":477680,"text":"This is the power of peer-to-peer\ncreating the new normal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482120,"text":"Next, we can flip doom to supportive."},{"time":485800,"text":"Rather than backfiring frames"},{"time":487720,"text":"such as disaster and cost,"},{"time":490720,"text":"we can reframe climate\nas being really about human health,"},{"time":496520,"text":"for instance, with plant-based\ndelicious burgers,"},{"time":500560,"text":"good for you and good for the climate."},{"time":503280,"text":"We can also reframe climate\nas being about new tech opportunities,"},{"time":506760,"text":"about safety and about new jobs."},{"time":511000,"text":"Solar jobs, for instance,\nare seeing an amazing growth."},{"time":513640,"text":"They just passed\nthe three million jobs mark."},{"time":517440,"text":"Psychology says,\nin order to create engagement,"},{"time":520039,"text":"we should present, on balance,"},{"time":522640,"text":"three positive or supportive framings"},{"time":526080,"text":"for each climate threat we mention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528680,"text":"Then we can flip dissonance"},{"time":531360,"text":"to simpler actions."},{"time":533520,"text":"This is often called nudging."},{"time":535000,"text":"The idea is, by better\nchoice architecture,"},{"time":540680,"text":"we can make the climate-friendly behaviors"},{"time":544520,"text":"default and convenient."},{"time":547480,"text":"Let me illustrate this. Take food waste."},{"time":550400,"text":"Food waste at buffets goes way down"},{"time":553840,"text":"if the plate or the box size\nis reduced a little,"},{"time":557440,"text":"because on the smaller plate it looks full"},{"time":560720,"text":"but in the big box it looks half empty,"},{"time":563440,"text":"so we put more in."},{"time":564920,"text":"So smaller plates make\na big difference for food waste."},{"time":568480,"text":"And there are hundreds\nof smart nudges like this."},{"time":571200,"text":"The point is, dissonance goes down\nas more behaviors are nudged."},{"time":575840,"text":"Then we can flip denial"},{"time":579480,"text":"by tailoring signals\nthat visualize our progress."},{"time":583200,"text":"We can provide motivating feedback"},{"time":585640,"text":"on how well we're doing\nwith our problem-solving."},{"time":589000,"text":"Say you improved your transport footprint"},{"time":591320,"text":"or cut energy waste in your buildings."},{"time":594480,"text":"Then one app that can\nshare this well is called Ducky."},{"time":598240,"text":"The idea is, you log your actions there,"},{"time":600200,"text":"and then you can see how well\nyour team or company is doing,"},{"time":604040,"text":"so you get real-time signals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606720,"text":"Finally, identity."},{"time":610120,"text":"We can flip identity with better stories."},{"time":613520,"text":"Our brain loves stories."},{"time":616880,"text":"So we need better stories\nof where we all want to go,"},{"time":619400,"text":"and we need more stories\nof the heroes and heroines"},{"time":622240,"text":"of all stripes that are\nmaking real change happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627560,"text":"I'm proud that my hometown of Oslo"},{"time":631320,"text":"is now embarking on a bold journey\nof electrifying all transport,"},{"time":635680,"text":"whether cars, bikes or buses."},{"time":639240,"text":"One of the people\nspearheading this is Christina Bu."},{"time":642760,"text":"She is heading the Electric\nVehicle Association for years"},{"time":646520,"text":"and she has been fighting every day."},{"time":648560,"text":"Now, the UK and France, India and China\nhave also announced plans"},{"time":653080,"text":"for ending the sales of fossil cars."},{"time":655920,"text":"Now, that's massive."},{"time":657800,"text":"And in Oslo, we can see\nhow enthusiastic EV owners"},{"time":662800,"text":"go and tell their electric stories\nto friends and neighbors"},{"time":666280,"text":"and bring them along."},{"time":667600,"text":"So we come full circle\nfrom story back to social."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673520,"text":"So thousands of climate communicators"},{"time":676720,"text":"are now starting to use these solutions"},{"time":679160,"text":"all over the world."},{"time":680800,"text":"It is clear, however,\nthat individual solutions"},{"time":684040,"text":"are not sufficient\nto solving climate alone,"},{"time":687920,"text":"but they do build\nstronger bottom-up support"},{"time":694000,"text":"for policies and solutions that can."},{"time":697240,"text":"That is why engaging people is so crucial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702120,"text":"I started this talk"},{"time":704320,"text":"with testing two ways\nof communicating climate with you."},{"time":709720,"text":"There is another way, too,"},{"time":711680,"text":"I'd like to share with you."},{"time":713800,"text":"It starts with reimagining climate itself"},{"time":716560,"text":"as the living air."},{"time":719080,"text":"Climate isn't really\nabout some abstract, distant climate"},{"time":722000,"text":"far, far away from us."},{"time":723280,"text":"It's about this air that surrounds us."},{"time":726720,"text":"This air, you can feel in this room, too,"},{"time":729800,"text":"the air that moves\nright now in your nostrils."},{"time":733800,"text":"This air is our earth's skin."},{"time":737320,"text":"It's amazingly thin,"},{"time":739440,"text":"compared to the size of the earth\nand the cosmos it shields us from,"},{"time":744120,"text":"far thinner than the skin of an apple"},{"time":746640,"text":"compared to its diameter."},{"time":749840,"text":"It may look infinite when we look up,"},{"time":753280,"text":"but the beautiful, breathable air\nis only like five to seven miles thin,"},{"time":758440,"text":"a fragile wrapping around a massive ball."},{"time":763640,"text":"Inside this skin,"},{"time":765520,"text":"we're all closely connected."},{"time":768920,"text":"The breath that you just took"},{"time":771360,"text":"contained around 400,000\nof the same argon atoms"},{"time":776120,"text":"that Gandhi breathed during his lifetime."},{"time":780960,"text":"Inside this thin,\nfluctuating, unsettled film,"},{"time":784440,"text":"all of life is nourished,\nprotected and held."},{"time":789440,"text":"It insulates and regulates temperatures"},{"time":791400,"text":"in a range that is just right\nfor water and for life as we know it,"},{"time":795440,"text":"and mediating between\nthe blue ocean and black eternity,"},{"time":799440,"text":"the clouds carry\nall the billions of tons of water"},{"time":802480,"text":"needed for the soils."},{"time":804480,"text":"The air fills the rivers,"},{"time":807400,"text":"stirs the waters,"},{"time":809040,"text":"waters the forests."},{"time":810920,"text":"With a global weirding of the weather,"},{"time":813040,"text":"there are good reasons\nfor feeling fear and despair,"},{"time":819120,"text":"yet we may first grieve\ntoday's sorry state and losses"},{"time":824480,"text":"and then turn to face the future\nwith sober eyes and determination."},{"time":830640,"text":"The new psychology of climate action"},{"time":833720,"text":"lies in letting go, not of science,"},{"time":836560,"text":"but of the crutches\nof abstractions and doomism,"},{"time":840600,"text":"and then choosing to tell the new stories."},{"time":843640,"text":"These are the stories"},{"time":845480,"text":"of how we achieve drawdown,\nthe reversing of global warming."},{"time":848840,"text":"These are the stories of the steps we take"},{"time":853080,"text":"as peoples, cities, companies"},{"time":856920,"text":"and public bodies"},{"time":858320,"text":"in caring for the air"},{"time":860240,"text":"in spite of strong headwinds."},{"time":864040,"text":"These are the stories of the steps we take"},{"time":866160,"text":"because they ground us\nin what we are as humans:"},{"time":870840,"text":"earthlings inside this living air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876640,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877880,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}